 <body>
  <p>Adobe Campaign allows you to create and send personalized messages on various channels and measure their effectiveness through dedicated reports.</p> 
  <p>It also lets you create cross-channel campaigns to better target recipients.</p> 
  <p>Four messaging channels are available in Adobe Campaign:</p> 
  <ul>
   <li><p>Email, presented in the <a href="../../channels/using/creating-an-email.md">Creating an email</a> section.</p> </li>
   <li><p>SMS, presented in the <a href="../../channels/using/creating-an-sms-message.md">Creating an SMS message</a> section.</p> </li>
   <li><p>Push notification, presented in the <a href="../../channels/using/creating-and-sending-a-push-notification.md">Creating a push notification</a> section.</p> </li>
   <li><p>Direct mail, presented in the <a href="../../channels/using/creating-the-direct-mail.md">Creating a direct mail delivery</a> section.</p> </li>
  </ul>
  <p>All marketing activities are based on a template. Templates can be used to configure frequently used properties, allowing you to gain time and consistency across your messaging strategy. </p> 
  <p>The functional administrator in charge of configuring the templates, can define, in the case of an email template:</p> 
  <ul>
   <li><p>The standard parameters of an email, such as the audience, schedule, or content.</p> </li>
   <li><p>The advanced parameters related to sending, validity, tracking, etc.</p> </li>
   <li><p>The pre-configuration parameters concerning targeting and personalization (targeting context).</p> </li>
  </ul>
  <p><strong>Related topics</strong>:</p> 
  <ul>
   <li><p> <a href="https://docs.campaign.adobe.com/doc/standard/getting_started/en/ACS_Deliverability.html">Optimizing your deliverability</a></p> </li>
  </ul>
